description:
&lt;p&gt;Burstead is a ward that specialises in Major Surgical, Urology and gynecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of learning opportunities and you would be welcomed into our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to offer this fantastic opportunity to join our knowledgeable and friendly team, Burstead is one of only a few wards that have enjoyed excellent recruitment and retention due to the pleasant and supportive working environment provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer nurses considerable opportunities that come with our highly skilled nursing team and support you to learn and achieve competency with a variety of extended nursing skills including central venous access devices, arterial lines, advanced respiratory support, advanced wound care/techniques, enteral and intravenous nutrition therapies and tracheostomy care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work very closely with excellent teams of Clinical Nurse Specialists from the Acute Pain Service, Colorectal, Urology, Stoma Nurses and Nutrition Team that provide support and expertise to all staff members to ensure we always provide and maintain the highest standards of care for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Burstead Ward receives excellent feedback from its nursing students, demonstrating our strengths in delivering excellent standards of care and support for patients and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Burstead ward supports and promotes our Trust Values of “Safe, Caring, Excellent, Together”. BTUH has been rated GOOD in the most recent Care Quality Commission visit. The ward continues to receive positive feedbacks from our nursing students, with some returning to substantive employment with us after their studies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
